<p>I have a working <a href="http://jejacks0n.github.io/mercury/" rel="nofollow">mercury</a> setup (image, full, snippets, simple)</p>  <p>I am trying to create a snippet, which contains an image and some text.  So i placed a input "file"-tag into my form. When I submit my multipart form within the snippet, the request takes place correctly. I break the process in the <code>MercuryController.snippet_preview</code>- action and I observe the <code>params</code>. But they do not contain the <code>image</code> params. All other params like <code>text_field</code> is working as it should and get submitted. </p>  <p><strong>How can I pick up the file into the request params? <em>(I am using rails 3.2.x)</em></strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;%= form_for 'options', {url: '', html: {multipart: true, class: 'form-horizontal', style: 'width:615px'}} do |f| %&gt;   // does not work   &lt;input id="options_image" name="options[image]" size="50" type="file" value="&lt;%= @options[:image] %&gt;"&gt;    // also tried    &lt;%= f.file_field :image %&gt;    // does work    &lt;input id="options_text" name="options[text]" size="50" type="text" value="&lt;%= @options[:text] %&gt;"&gt;    &lt;input id="options_textarea" name="options[textarea]" size="50" type="text" value="&lt;%= @options[:textarea] %&gt;"&gt;     &lt;input class="btn btn-primary" name="commit" type="submit" value="Insert Snippet"/&gt; &lt;% end %&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Here is the result of the observed params:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/NTyHJ.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/NTyHJ.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>And this is the console output</p>  <pre><code>Started POST "/mercury/snippets/image_example/preview.html" for 127.0.0.1 at 2015-09-10 03:18:13 +0200  Processing by MercuryController#snippet_preview as HTML   Parameters: {"options"=&gt;{"title"=&gt;"", "textarea"=&gt;""}, "name"=&gt;"image_example"}    Rendered mercury/snippets/image_example/preview.html.erb